  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A new operation technique was established (&quot;reversed gap technique&quot; for implantation of total
      knee arthroplasties. Based on the encouraging results of a pilot study, the clinical outcome
      shall be evaluated using the conventional &quot;gap technique&quot; as control in a RCT study.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
